f(x) = -3+2\cos(x)
g(x) = \cos(x-\dfrac{1}{4}\pi)-2 
s(x)=f(x)+g(x)
d(x)=f(x)-g(x)
g(x)=\cos(x-\frac{\pi}{4})-2=\cos x\cos \frac{\pi}{4} + \sin x\sin \frac{\pi}{4} -2
=\frac{1}{\sqrt2}\cos x+\frac{1}{\sqrt2}\sin x -2
s(x)=f(x)+g(x)=3+2\cos x + \frac{1}{\sqrt2}\cos x+\frac{1}{\sqrt2}\sin x -2
=-5+\frac{2\sqrt2+1}{\sqrt2}\cos x+\frac{1}{\sqrt2}\sin x
r\cos y=\frac{2\sqrt2+1}{\sqrt2}
r\sin y = \frac{1}{\sqrt2} 
\frac{2\sqrt2+1}{\sqrt2}\cos x+\frac{1}{\sqrt2}\sin x=r(\cos y\cos x+\sin y\sin x)
=r\cos(x-y)
r^2=\frac{(2\sqrt2+1)^2+1}{2}=5+2\sqrt2
\tan y=\frac{1}{2\sqrt2+1}\implies y=\tan^{-1}(\frac{1}{2\sqrt2+1})
s(x)=f(x)+g(x)=-5+\sqrt{5+2\sqrt2}\cos(x-\tan^{-1}(\frac{1}{2\sqrt2+1}))
